                            <comment id="13462221" author="mackrorysd" created="Mon, 24 Sep 2012 22:48:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;log4j.threshold and hive.root.logger specify two different levels. Should they actually be the same, in reality or should only one be paramterized? Which would be most intuitive considering how this file gets used?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13462228" author="cwsteinbach" created="Mon, 24 Sep 2012 22:53:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Generally speaking they should be the same. The way you have it setup in hive-log4j.properties looks like the right approach to me.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
